==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Propiolic
<hw>Pro`pi*ol"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Propi</ets>onic + tetr<ets>olic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an organic acid
(called also <xex>propargylic</xex> acid) of the acetylene or tetrolic
series, analogous to propionic acid, and obtained as a white crystalline
substance.</def><-- also called 2-propynoic acid, and
acetylenecarboxylic acid. <chform>C3H2O2</chform>,
<chform>CH.C.COOH</chform> -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propionate</ent>⟦br⟧
